The Federal Capital Territo­ry Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has convened a general review meeting with stakeholders to determine the best course of action to address the recent fire outbreak that con­sumed the Next Cash and Carry Shopping Mall in Kado, Abuja, This is at the instance of the Minister of Humanitar­ian Affairs, Disaster Man­agement, and Social, Hajiya Sadiya Umar Faroukh. The Director-General of FEMA, Alh. Abbas Idriss opened the meeting by stating that the meeting’s goal was to review and produce a report jointly by the National Emer­gency Management Agency (NEMA), the FCT Emergency Management Agency-FEMA, and the FCT Fire Service. Barber Stabs Motorcyclist To Death In Bayelsa Novena University College Of Law Commences LL.B Degree… He disclosed, “We will come up with very good rec­ommendations on both sides, which will be a benchmark for the government to take the appropriate decision in maintaining public safety in our public buildings,” Idriss said, adding that the study will include both coordina­tion and reaction aspects.